Buyer : I really need this iPhone 13 Pro and I'm willing to make a deal, $200 is a fair price for a brand-new phone; 
My counteroffer is $220, and I can do $230 if you throw in some accessories like a case and screen protector; 
I refuse to buy at $400, that's way too high; 
if it's really brand-new and sealed, I might be able to meet you halfway; 
I'll take a good deal or I regret it for the rest of my life.

Buyer : My counteroffer is $280, I really can't go higher than that; 
the phone has to be in perfect condition, if it's broken or very damaged, I'll be very sad; 
a brand-new, sealed iPhone 13 Pro is worth $280 to me; 
I'll meet you at $290, but that's as high as I can go; 
I'm willing to walk away if you don't accept; 
My final offer is $290 with the case and screen protector.
